<% layout("layouts/boilerplate.ejs") %>

<div class="container mt-5">
  <h1 class="mb-4 text-center">Privacy Policy</h1>

  <div class="mb-4">
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy outlines how the <strong>BCA Tech Team</strong> handles user data and ensures the safety and confidentiality of all registered students.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h4 class="mb-3">1. Who We Are</h4>
  <p>
    We are a student-led technical team under the department, focusing on web development and digital solutions. This platform is exclusively for pre-approved BCA students who wish to participate in team activities, access resources, and stay updated on events.
  </p>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">2. What Data We Collect</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Student Name</li>
    <li>Username / Enrollment ID</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Profile picture (optional)</li>
    <li>Event participation logs</li>
    <li>Resources accessed and downloaded</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">3. How We Use Your Data</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>To allow access to the dashboard and learning resources</li>
    <li>To manage event participation and registrations</li>
    <li>To improve content based on user interest</li>
    <li>To maintain a secure student-only platform</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">4. Data Protection & Security</h4>
  <p>
    All student data is securely stored and only accessible by authorized members of the tech team. We do not share your data with any third parties.
  </p>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">5. Image and Media Policy</h4>
  <p>
    Event photos and other media uploaded on this platform are only for internal viewing and are used to promote transparency and record participation. If you wish to have your image removed, please contact the admin.
  </p>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">6. Your Responsibilities</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the platform respectfully and ethically</li>
    <li>Do not share login credentials</li>
    <li>Do not upload unauthorized content</li>
    <li>Inform admins in case of suspicious activity</li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="mt-4 mb-3">7. Your Rights</h4>
  <p>
    You can request to update or delete your data at any time by contacting the Web Department Admin. We respect your privacy and take data concerns seriously.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-5 text-muted text-end">
    <small>Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %></small>
  </div>
</div>
